article.description: Tanner Leissner scored 21 points, Iba Camara added 15 points and 16 rebounds and New Hampshire rallied from an 11-point second-half deficit to beat Maine 71-56 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Leissner, Camara lead New Hampshire to 71-56 win over Maine
article.linkText: Leissner, Camara lead New Hampshire to 71-56 win over Maine
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Tanner Leissner scored 21 points, Iba Camara added 15 points and 16 rebounds and New Hampshire rallied from an 11-point second-half deficit to beat Maine 71-56 on Thursday night. Elijah Jordan had 13 points and Evan Horn scored 10 for New Hampshire (10-15, 6-5 America East). Jordan hit a jumper to give the Wildcats a 15-14 lead midway through the first half, but New Hampshire missed 24 of its next 26 field-goal attempts as the Black Bears opened a 37-26 lead early in the second half. Leissner hit a 3 -- the Wildcats' first field goal in more than 10 1/2 minutes -- to spark a 14-2 spurt that gave New Hampshire a one-point lead with 13:29 to play. Andrew Fleming made a jumper and then hit two free throws to pull Maine within two points with 7:19 left, but Camara scored 12 points during a 17-4 run to close the game. Aaron Calixte had 16 points and Fleming scored 12 for Maine (6-20, 3-8). New Hampshire outrebounded the Black Bears 47-32, including 16-3 on the offensive glass, and outscored them 13-3 on second-chance points.
